00:24.791 --> 00:27.851
<i>[ Whistle Blowing ]</i>

00:30.330 --> 00:32.229
[ Beeping ]

00:37.971 --> 00:39.871
## [Jazzy Solo ]

00:59.959 --> 01:01.859
[ Beeping ]

01:01.961 --> 01:03.861
[ Tires Screeching ]

01:05.230 --> 01:07.165
D'oh!
[ Screams ]

01:25.351 --> 01:28.582
This is Kent Brockman,
live at the Monty Burns Casino.

01:28.688 --> 01:31.589
Moments from now, ''the house
that social security checks built''...

01:31.691 --> 01:36.094
will be demolished to make way
for a casino-themed family hotel.

01:36.196 --> 01:38.426
This must be heartbreaking for you, sir.

01:38.531 --> 01:40.726
I'm just thinking of my employees-

01:40.834 --> 01:44.668
All the cardsharps,
bottom dealers and shills.

01:44.771 --> 01:47.672
- Where will they go?
- They're managing
your chain of nursing homes, sir.

01:47.774 --> 01:49.674
Excellent.

01:49.776 --> 01:52.939
Gone are such headliners
as Little Timmy and the Shebangs...

01:53.046 --> 01:56.812
the Shebangs, and the New Shebangs,
featuring Big Timmy.

01:56.916 --> 01:59.282
Remember how excited
we were when this place opened?

01:59.385 --> 02:01.546
Then a week later
we just forgot about it.

02:01.654 --> 02:04.589
I'm surprised they bothered to move it
when they moved the town.

02:04.691 --> 02:06.591
Oh, I can explain that. You see-

02:06.693 --> 02:10.322
<i>Five, four, three, two-</i>

02:10.430 --> 02:12.796
All right! Here comes the implosion.

02:12.899 --> 02:15.595
''Implosion''? But I thought you said-

02:15.702 --> 02:17.602
[ Crowd Clamoring ]

02:17.704 --> 02:20.730
- Hockey puck!
- [ Chuckling ]

02:20.840 --> 02:22.831
Don Rickles zinged you, Marge.

02:25.411 --> 02:27.106
Dust!

02:29.015 --> 02:31.279
Eat my dust, dust. Oops.

02:31.384 --> 02:33.511
<i>- [ Crash ]
- [ Man Screams ]</i>

02:33.620 --> 02:35.850
<i>[ Lisa ]
Dad, we hit Don Rickles.</i>

02:35.955 --> 02:38.924
<i>[ Man ] I'm okay, but the Puerto Rican
guy's trying to steal your hubcaps.</i>

02:39.025 --> 02:42.085
<i>[ Chuckles ]
Just kiddin; I'm a nice guy.</i>

02:47.400 --> 02:49.561
We'd better stop
and get the car washed.

02:49.669 --> 02:51.967
Aw, what's the rush?
Might rain next week.

02:52.071 --> 02:54.938
Hey, Homer, your car's kind of dirty.

02:55.041 --> 02:57.066
Really? You think
I should get it washed?

02:57.177 --> 03:01.341
- Yeah, maybe.
- [ Tires Squealing ]

03:01.447 --> 03:04.211
You listen to your friends,
but you never listen to me.

03:04.317 --> 03:06.649
Hey, that's great.

03:06.753 --> 03:09.483
All right, young 'uns, bath time.

03:09.589 --> 03:13.355
Cover up your eyes and drop your britches.
Who wants wax?

03:13.459 --> 03:15.359
- [ Children ] Me!
- [ Howls ]

03:15.461 --> 03:17.691
I insist you take special care
with my collection...

03:17.797 --> 03:19.856
of valuable and humorous
bumper stickers-

03:19.966 --> 03:21.763
Particularly this one...

03:21.868 --> 03:24.530
which was given to me
by a Harrison Ford look-alike.

03:24.637 --> 03:26.571
<i>No hablo ingles, senor.</i>

03:28.675 --> 03:30.734
<i>[ Machinery Whirring ]</i>

03:32.312 --> 03:34.212
Oh.

03:34.314 --> 03:36.339
<i>##[ Muzak On P.A.]</i>

03:36.449 --> 03:38.679
Wow. You can't find
this stuff anywhere.

03:38.785 --> 03:41.652
Seals and Crofts?
Pablo Cruise? Air Supply?

03:41.754 --> 03:44.484
Whoa, ho. Loggins and Oates.

03:44.591 --> 03:46.491
And it's free.

03:46.593 --> 03:48.493
I've never heard of these bands, Mom.

03:48.595 --> 03:50.790
- What kind of music do they play?
- Crap-Rock?

03:50.897 --> 03:52.797
- No.
- Wuss-Rock?

03:52.899 --> 03:55.424
- That's it.
- [ Bell Dings ]

03:55.535 --> 03:59.062
Ten dollars? What is this,
a car wash for millionaires?

03:59.172 --> 04:01.640
- Throw hot wax on him, Dad.
- Howdy, Homer.

04:01.741 --> 04:03.641
Five dollars, please.

04:03.743 --> 04:06.940
Hey, how did ''Churchy LaFemme''
get half price?

04:07.046 --> 04:11.983
- Senior citizens' discount.
- [ Scoffs ] ''Senior citizen''? Flanders?

04:12.085 --> 04:14.519
Well, we'll see about that.

04:14.621 --> 04:14.721
<i>##[ Organ ]</i>

04:14.721 --> 04:17.120
<i>##[ Organ ]</i>

04:17.223 --> 04:22.024
<i>And once again, tithing
is 1 0% off the top.</i>

04:22.128 --> 04:24.688
That's gross income, not net.

04:24.797 --> 04:27.891
- Please, people, don't force us to audit.
- [ Murmuring ]

04:28.001 --> 04:30.936
Now, I'm going to pass this
around a second time.

04:31.037 --> 04:32.937
Brother Ned, if you'll do the honors-

04:33.039 --> 04:35.200
I wouldn't do that, Reverend.

04:35.308 --> 04:40.041
You see, ''Saint Flanders''
is as crooked as you or me.

04:40.146 --> 04:41.943
[ Murmuring ]

04:42.048 --> 04:43.948
That's right.

04:44.050 --> 04:47.679
It's my sad duty to rat out this man
for defrauding a car wash.

04:47.787 --> 04:52.247
How, you ask?
With a phony senior-discount card.

04:52.358 --> 04:55.088
- [ Murmuring ]
- Well, that's not quite true.

04:55.194 --> 04:58.925
Did you or did you not use a senior citizen
discount card at said car wash?

04:59.032 --> 05:02.900
- Well, I did, but-
- Now, I'm not a fancy, big-city lawyer-

05:03.002 --> 05:06.199
- [ All Gasp ]
- But it seems to me that a senior citizen...

05:06.306 --> 05:08.399
has to be over 5 5.

05:08.508 --> 05:10.408
- Isn't that so?
- Well, yes.

05:10.510 --> 05:13.035
- And you are how old?
- [ Sighs ]

05:13.146 --> 05:16.946
I suppose, if you must know,
I'm-Well, I'm- I'm 60.

05:17.050 --> 05:20.417
<i>- [ Lenny ] God, he looks so good.
- [ Moe ] He looks unbelievable.</i>

05:20.520 --> 05:23.887
What's your secret, Flanders?
Goat placenta? Monkey sweat?

05:23.990 --> 05:27.551
- Some kind of electric hat?
- Holy water? It's holy water, right?

05:27.660 --> 05:29.560
Aah! It burns!

05:29.662 --> 05:32.529
Listen, folks. There's no magic formula.

05:32.632 --> 05:34.532
I just follow the three C's-

05:34.634 --> 05:36.534
Clean living, chewing thoroughly...

05:36.636 --> 05:38.831
and a daily dose of vitamin church.

05:38.938 --> 05:42.374
- [ Groaning ]
- And, of course, I resist all the major urges.

05:42.475 --> 05:45.171
- All of them?
- You mean you've never splurged...

05:45.278 --> 05:47.576
and, say, eaten
an entire birthday cake...

05:47.680 --> 05:49.580
- then blamed it on the dog?
- Oh?

05:49.682 --> 05:52.845
You've never licked maple syrup
off your lover's stomach?

05:52.952 --> 05:56.547
- [ Skinner Groans ]
- You've never snuck out
of church to break into cars?

05:56.656 --> 05:58.851
No, no and double no.

05:58.958 --> 06:00.892
I haven't done any
of those things, folks.

06:00.993 --> 06:03.257
You name it, I haven't done it.

06:03.363 --> 06:05.263
Geez, Flanders, you're 60 years old...

06:05.365 --> 06:07.265
and you haven't lived
a day in your life.

06:07.367 --> 06:09.835
Yeah, even the boy in the bubble
had a deck of cards.

06:09.936 --> 06:12.837
- [ Chattering ]
- Hmm.

06:15.007 --> 06:16.907
Can you believe it?

06:17.009 --> 06:20.376
It almost seemed like those folks
were making fun of old Steady Neddie.

06:20.480 --> 06:23.005
Well, you may be a bit cautious,
but what's wrong with that?

06:23.116 --> 06:26.051
Some people like chunky
peanut butter, some like smooth.

06:26.152 --> 06:29.918
Mm-hmm, and some people just
steer clear of that whole hornets' nest.

06:30.022 --> 06:33.549
I'll stick with just plain white bread,
thank you very much, maybe with a-

06:33.659 --> 06:36.287
[ Together]
Glass of water on the side for dippin'.

06:36.396 --> 06:39.388
- [ Brakes Squeal ]
- Gosh darn it.

06:39.499 --> 06:42.559
Am I that pre-diddly-ictable?

06:42.668 --> 06:46.695
[ Sighs ]
I've wasted my whole dang-diddly life.

06:46.806 --> 06:48.967
<i>- ##[ Rock On Radio ]
- Hey there!</i>

06:49.075 --> 06:53.341
Look at that. Everyone's livin'
it up except Ned.

06:54.447 --> 06:56.881
Help! We're being carjacked.

06:56.983 --> 06:59.008
Don't get clever, old man.

06:59.118 --> 07:01.052
Now take us to Dress Barn.

07:05.391 --> 07:07.552
<i>[ Maude ]
Where have you been, Neddie?</i>

07:07.660 --> 07:10.891
<i>In the bathroom-
not trimmin' my mustache.</i>

07:10.997 --> 07:12.897
What do you think?

07:12.999 --> 07:15.160
Do I remind you of
troubled troubadour David Crosby?

07:15.268 --> 07:19.295
- No, you remind me of silly billy Ned Flanders.
- [ Laughing ]

07:19.405 --> 07:22.374
- Would a silly billy sit like this?
- [ Snap ]

07:22.475 --> 07:25.000
- Ooh!
- Rod, Call Dr. Stein.

07:25.111 --> 07:28.137
<i>All right, Bart- Fire in the hole.</i>

07:29.248 --> 07:32.775
[ Chuckles ]
Okay, no more gasoline.

07:32.885 --> 07:36.719
- Hmm.
- ## [ Humming ]

07:38.157 --> 07:40.352
Full power.

07:40.460 --> 07:42.325
Never a dull moment, huh, Homer?

07:42.428 --> 07:44.726
You got that right.
Throw on the mesquite, Bart.

07:44.831 --> 07:47.026
Mesquite it is.

07:49.101 --> 07:53.299
You know, this may sound just a teensy bit
insane in the ol' membrane, Homer...

07:53.406 --> 07:55.966
but I was wondering if you
could show me how to have some fun.

07:56.075 --> 07:57.975
Well, well, well.

07:58.077 --> 08:00.045
So Flawless Flanders needs help...

08:00.146 --> 08:02.114
from Stinky Pants Simpson.

08:02.215 --> 08:03.978
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, I guess I do.

08:04.083 --> 08:05.983
Welly, welly, welly.

08:06.085 --> 08:10.454
-Mr. Clean wants to hang with Dirty Dingus Magee.
-How about it, Homer?

08:10.556 --> 08:13.753
Will you teach me the secret
of your intoxicating lust for life?

08:13.860 --> 08:16.954
- Wellity, wellity, wellity.
- Stop that!

08:17.063 --> 08:18.963
Will you help me or not?

08:19.065 --> 08:20.965
<i>- [ Can Clanks ]
- Let's do it.</i>

08:22.034 --> 08:23.934
<i>- [ Groans ]
- So what about all this meat?</i>

08:24.036 --> 08:25.936
<i>Aw, the missus will clean that up.</i>

08:26.038 --> 08:28.233
Now it's Marge's time to shine.

08:29.675 --> 08:32.472
First of all, I get
five dollars a day, plus expenses.

08:32.578 --> 08:35.479
- Seems fair.
- And I'll need your signature...

08:35.581 --> 08:37.481
here, here...

08:37.582 --> 08:39.778
and initial here.

08:41.087 --> 08:43.317
[ Chuckles ]
You're not really giving my father...

08:43.422 --> 08:45.390
- power of attorney, are you?
- Of course I-

08:45.491 --> 08:47.823
[ Gasps ]
Oh, my stars. I can't do that.

08:47.927 --> 08:50.487
Well, that's unfortunate. Really is.

08:50.596 --> 08:52.962
[ Sighs ]
All right.

08:53.065 --> 08:54.965
Congratulations.

08:55.067 --> 08:57.433
Welcome to the Homer Simpson Program.

08:57.537 --> 08:59.437
So what happens next?

08:59.539 --> 09:01.507
One day soon I will come for you...

09:01.607 --> 09:03.507
and then the game will begin.

09:03.609 --> 09:05.509
Could be in the middle of the night.

09:05.611 --> 09:08.171
It could be when
you least expect it.

09:08.281 --> 09:10.146
Or whatever's good for you.
I don't care.

09:10.249 --> 09:12.945
Okay, Homer, I'm ready to learn.

09:13.052 --> 09:15.919
What's the first lesson?
Just gimme the topic sentence.

09:17.123 --> 09:19.148
Gimme that! That's your problem.

09:19.258 --> 09:21.158
You're livin' up here.

09:21.260 --> 09:25.026
You gotta live down here,
in the impulse zone.

09:25.131 --> 09:28.191
If you wanna be like me,
you gotta make snap decisions-

09:28.301 --> 09:30.667
- Like this!
- [ Tires Squealing ]

09:30.770 --> 09:32.931
We're going to break the bank...

09:33.039 --> 09:35.735
at the Monty Burns Casino.

09:35.841 --> 09:37.968
Homer, they blew that up yesterday.

09:38.077 --> 09:40.375
<i>- [ Homer ] Oh,yeah, right.
- [ Ned Whimpers ]</i>

09:40.479 --> 09:42.845
Then we're goin' to Las Vegas-

09:42.949 --> 09:46.942
- Which is actually back in that direction.
- [ Tires Squeal ]

09:50.189 --> 09:52.282
## [ Ad-libs Song ]

09:59.298 --> 10:01.425
That sure was a fun trip to Las Vegas.

10:01.534 --> 10:03.434
Eh, too many kids.

10:04.537 --> 10:06.903
Ooh. It's goin' on 8:30.

10:07.006 --> 10:09.304
I better call Maude
and tell her where I am.

10:09.408 --> 10:12.900
Relax. I called her
from the gas station.

10:13.012 --> 10:16.413
- Thanks, buddy.
- [ Snickers ] Sucker.

10:43.576 --> 10:46.272
Gee, Homer, this all looks
so garish.

10:46.379 --> 10:49.109
<i>- [ Monkey Chattering ]
- [ Elephant Trumpeting ]</i>

10:50.683 --> 10:53.948
Oh! The lights, the noise, the letter ''X.''

10:54.053 --> 10:56.351
It's-It's all designed
to inflame the senses.

10:56.455 --> 10:59.754
I'm overstimulated.
I gotta get out of this town.

10:59.859 --> 11:02.020
I don't think so.

11:02.128 --> 11:05.120
I think you'll find
escape is quite impossible.

11:05.231 --> 11:07.131
No, I got it.

11:07.233 --> 11:10.134
Oh! Would you like to be
in the audience for my infomercial?

11:10.236 --> 11:12.898
[ Screams ]

11:14.006 --> 11:15.906
- Help me!
- [ Screams ]

11:16.008 --> 11:18.909
My daughter's not talented.
[ Groans ]

11:19.011 --> 11:20.979
[ Tires Squealing ]

11:22.448 --> 11:24.348
<i>[ Crowd Cheering ]</i>

11:24.450 --> 11:26.350
Hey- Lance Murdock.

11:26.452 --> 11:28.352
[ Revving ]

11:28.454 --> 11:31.355
If he's not careful, his scooter
could roll right down that ramp.

11:31.457 --> 11:34.426
He's a daredevil, Ned.
He laughs at death.

11:34.527 --> 11:38.588
Whoa. When I wanna laugh,
I'll take Bob Saget, thank you very much.

11:38.698 --> 11:43.067
<i>And now, the indestructible
Lance Murdock will jump his ''SuiCycle';..</i>

11:43.169 --> 11:45.467
over an audience member-

11:45.571 --> 11:49.405
<i>And he'll do it while attempting
to open a locked safe...</i>

11:49.508 --> 11:51.408
<i>on his head.</i>

11:51.510 --> 11:53.637
Any volunteers?

11:53.746 --> 11:56.442
- Ooh, ooh, ooh! Pick him. Pick him.
- Homer, no.

11:56.549 --> 11:58.517
I wanna do something exciting...

11:58.617 --> 12:01.950
but I can't just go
from zero to 30 like that.

12:02.054 --> 12:04.522
- I-I could be killed.
- Fine. I'll do it.

12:04.623 --> 12:07.717
- Where do you want me?
- On the ''X.''

12:09.295 --> 12:11.388
You mean the one with the red paint?

12:11.497 --> 12:13.397
Uh, yeah, paint.

12:13.499 --> 12:16.332
Now, it's of critical
importance that you don't-

12:16.435 --> 12:19.802
Yeah, yeah, yeah. I'll figure it out.
This isn't rocket science.

12:19.905 --> 12:23.102
Well, actually, there are
several rockets mounted to the-

12:23.209 --> 12:26.110
<i>- Boring.
- [ Crowd Cheering ]</i>

12:28.681 --> 12:31.946
[ Revving ]

12:32.051 --> 12:34.849
<i>[ Announcer ]
Okay, he's cleared the ring of fire...</i>

12:34.954 --> 12:39.186
<i>passed the ring of ice,
over the dog do stick.</i>

12:39.291 --> 12:43.125
<i>- He's cracked the safe.
- Hey, Flanders, don't spill my beer.</i>

12:43.229 --> 12:45.288
Oh, God! Lay down. Lay down.

12:45.397 --> 12:48.594
[ Screaming ]

12:48.701 --> 12:50.760
- Clear!
- [ Electrical Crackling ]

12:50.870 --> 12:53.065
He's all right, folks.

12:53.172 --> 12:55.140
[ Cheering ]

12:55.241 --> 12:57.334
Okeydoke. Let's hit the tables.

12:57.443 --> 13:00.139
My God, Homer, watching you risk your life...

13:00.246 --> 13:02.976
turned my beat box
all the way up to ''rumba.''

13:03.082 --> 13:05.380
I was praying you'd be safe...

13:05.484 --> 13:09.181
but t-to be honest, part of me
wanted to see you get splattered.

13:09.288 --> 13:13.987
- Oh, I think someone just had
his first taste of bloodlust.
- Hmm.

13:14.093 --> 13:17.620
- [ Clicking,Jingling ]
- Let's see. What's Marge's birthday?

13:17.730 --> 13:19.857
Barney's is July 1 5, same as Lassie's...

13:19.965 --> 13:23.196
so Marge must be 50- Oh, forget it.

13:23.302 --> 13:26.271
- Flanders, what's your birthday?
- Oh, leave me out of this, Homer.

13:26.372 --> 13:28.499
Games of chance are strictly forbidden
by Deuteronomy 7.

13:28.607 --> 13:30.871
Seven, eh?

13:33.913 --> 13:37.246
<i>- [ Man ] Seven a winner.
- Way to go, Flanders.</i>

13:37.349 --> 13:39.249
The Bible's finally pulling its weight.

13:39.351 --> 13:41.251
Got any more holy numbers?

13:41.353 --> 13:43.253
Oh, I've got a bunch, Homer, but-

13:43.355 --> 13:45.619
I just don't feel right.

13:45.724 --> 13:48.420
Oh, Lord, what should I do?

13:48.527 --> 13:51.223
<i>- [ Man With Deep Voice ] Keep Gaming.
- What?</i>

13:51.330 --> 13:55.994
- It means gambling. Keep gambling.
- Oh. Right-eo.

13:56.101 --> 13:59.366
- One betting disk, please.
- ''One betting disk, please.''

13:59.471 --> 14:02.133
Watch and learn.

14:04.543 --> 14:07.637
- And 1 4 black.
- Well, there you go.

14:07.746 --> 14:09.714
- Now, how about a drink?
- [ Stammers ]

14:12.117 --> 14:14.517
How do you do it, Homer?

14:14.620 --> 14:17.214
How do you silence
that little voice that says, ''Think.''

14:17.323 --> 14:20.349
- You mean Lisa?
- Oh, no. I mean common sense.

14:20.459 --> 14:24.088
Oh, that. That can be treated
with our good friend alcohol.

14:24.196 --> 14:26.687
You might want to write that down.
Where the hell's your notebook?

14:26.799 --> 14:28.824
- You threw it out the-
- Never mind.Just pay attention.

14:28.934 --> 14:31.926
- Slave girl? Oh, slave girl.
- [ Ice Cubes Tinkling ]

14:32.037 --> 14:35.473
- More libations, my imperial conquerors?
- What?

14:35.574 --> 14:39.203
- More booze?
- Oh, yeah. Two more of these, please.

14:39.311 --> 14:41.245
- [ Beeping ]
- And for you, Ned?

14:41.347 --> 14:44.111
I'll have a Shirley-
No, a virgin-

14:44.216 --> 14:46.207
No, make it a children's-

14:46.318 --> 14:49.845
Oh, what the heck.
You only live once.

14:49.955 --> 14:53.413
Give me a white wine spritzer.

14:53.525 --> 14:55.425
<i>[ Echoing ]
Spritzer-</i>

14:58.597 --> 15:01.395
<i>[ Loud Snoring ]</i>

15:06.138 --> 15:08.038
- [ Groans ]
- [ Snoring Continues ]

15:08.140 --> 15:10.040
Oh, my goodness, Homer.

15:10.142 --> 15:12.110
- Wake up.
- [ Mumbling ]

15:13.979 --> 15:16.038
Oh, look at this place.

15:16.148 --> 15:19.140
Hoo. We must have
really painted the town last night.

15:19.251 --> 15:22.220
I have a pounding headache,
my mouth tastes like vomit...

15:22.321 --> 15:24.221
and I don't remember a thing.

15:24.323 --> 15:26.223
Welcome to my world.

15:26.325 --> 15:28.225
Oh, I did it!

15:28.327 --> 15:31.854
I conquered my fears
and I made up for a lot of lost living.

15:31.964 --> 15:35.229
- And I owe it all to the Homer Simpson Program.
- The what, now?

15:35.334 --> 15:37.461
<i>[ Woman ]
Well, it's about time you two woke up.</i>

15:37.569 --> 15:39.469
Well, of course. It-
[ Screams ]

15:39.571 --> 15:42.369
- Who are you?
- Who am I?

15:42.474 --> 15:44.942
I'm Mrs. Ned Flanders.

15:45.044 --> 15:46.978
- G'ah!
- [ Laughs ]

